    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Williams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 13, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 11th of July last,
                            No. 4, transmitting a copy of the correspondence which passed between
                            yourself and Prince Kung upon the subject of the assassination of the
                            late President Lincoln, has been received. The sentiments expressed by
                            his excellency regarding the melancholy occurrence referred to are
                            highly appreciated.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Wells Williams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.,</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
